      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUSSO (8) settled midfield in the run and boxed on to finish there when 4th (20.21) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can make amends. HERE COMES SHAKA (2) stuck on well last time to finish 1.3 lengths back in second (20.09) at this track in a Other over 342m. Overdue and gets his chance. FLYING EMBERS (4) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 19.95 beating Cool It Mister. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings seven times from 14 starts. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. BONMATI (5) cannot be ruled out.",
